## Git Commits
- Never commit without explicit user instruction
- Commit messages in English only

## Code Style
- Use English for comments/docs
- Use descriptive variable names (no single letters)
- Use named callbacks in JSX handlers (not anonymous arrows)

## React Components
- Component folder: PascalCase name, direct export (no index.ts)
- Subfolders: `components/`, `hooks/`, `helpers/`
- Hook files: CamelCase matching hook name (`useHook.ts`, not `use-hook.ts`)
- Types: centralized `typing.ts` in component folder
- Dialogs: use `useHashDialog` from `@/hooks/shared` with unique ID
- Dialog buttons: `flex-row justify-end gap-2` for mobile

## Utilities
- Prefer Lodash (`lodash-es`) over custom utils

## Database
- **ALWAYS backup before dangerous operations**
- Backup command: `./scripts/backup-db.sh` or `npm run db:backup`
- Dangerous ops: DROP, TRUNCATE, mass DELETE, schema changes, migrations
- Workflow: backup → verify ✅ → proceed → inform user of backup path
- If backup fails, DO NOT proceed
